	<div class="py-20">
	<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
	<div class="mb-16 max-w-xl mx-auto text-center">
	<span class="greenhead">Frequently Asked Questions</span>
	</div>
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
	<ul class="space-y-4 lg:space-y-6">
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>We have multiple inlets per house. Should we re-plumb and unify the lines?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">Not necessary. Our system is designed to measure on multiple inlets as-is and aggregate the usage and billing under one connection. Having said that, if it is more economical and simple to merge, we will help you with that as well.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>How long does it take to install?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">Once you place the order, we need a lead time of 2-3 weeks to plan and start installation. Installation itself would typically take 6-8 weeks based on size of your community.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>Is there a minimum order quantity (MoQ)?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">There is no MoQ. But then, due to the way our network is designed, our systems are more cost effective with more meters.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>Is anything required from the Company/RWA/Community?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">One point to draw AC power from is required. We will take care of the rest turn-key, including power backup and internet connectivity.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>Are these for commercial or residential?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">We roll with them all - factories, colleges, commercial buildings, apartments, villas, row-houses and such. If you need measuring water, we're here to help you.</p>
	</li>
	<li class="faq">
	<button class="faqhead">
	<span>What happens if power/internet is down?</span><div></div>
	</button>
	<p class="hidden">If power is down, our backup system keeps running the meter for up to two days. If network connectivity is down, readings are accumulated in the gateway until connectivity is restored.</p>
	</li>
	</ul>
